information.transaction: Variant entry, mapped to genes and transcripts. id: string to identifty transaction in samples.
information.genomic_location: chromosome and position of the variant on DNA level. build: used coordinate version
information.reference_allele: The expected reference in the human genome
information.alternative_allele: The observed allele in the sample
information.gene: HGNC symbol of the affected gene
information.transcript: Affected transcript. We selected a reference transcript for each gene. In case the variant only affects alternate transcripts, the first transcript listed in ANNOVAR output is shown.
information.protein_variant: HGVS recommended syntax of protein level alteration,corresponding to the listed transcript variant
information.protein_effect: Effect on the listed transcript, as reported by ANNOVAR. RefGene version used: 2015-12-12
information.protein_impact: Category based on protein_effect values. HIGH: stopgain,stoploss,frameshift,splicing. MEDIUM: non-synomous, non-frameshift. LOW: synonymous, UTR, intronic
information.cohort_frequency: Frequency of the variant in the current sample cohort.
information.exac_frequency: Frequency of the variant in the Non-Psychiatric sub-release of ExAC. Consider variants below 0.01 as RARE.
information.cadd_phred: Prediction of pathogenicity. Interpretataion: variant is in top 100*10^-(x/10) percent of most damaging variants, simulated genome wide. Consider variants above 20 as likely damaging
information.affected_domains: if any, a manually curated list of affected protein domains. source: origin of the annotation.
